> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.

**Goal:** Add a `Site` domain that lets users register any website, crawl it with BFS, capture DOM + screenshot baselines, and detect regressions by comparing later runs against the baseline. The existing `Scenario` flow is untouched.

**Architecture:** Add a parallel domain (`Site`) with its own types, manager, crawler, runner, diff engine, API routes, and UI. Reuse only `chromium`/Playwright primitives via a new `lib/browser-bootstrap.ts`. Persistence is plain JSON files under `data/sites/<siteId>/...`. Visual diff uses `pixelmatch` + `pngjs`; DOM diff uses `diff` after deterministic normalization in `page.evaluate`. Auth is handled by Playwright `storageState`.

**Tech Stack:** Next.js 14 (App Router) 쨌 TypeScript 쨌 Playwright (chromium) 쨌 pixelmatch 쨌 pngjs 쨌 diff 쨌 jsdom (test only) 쨌 Node `node:test`-style unit tests under `tests/unit/` (existing convention) 쨌 Tailwind / shadcn-style UI components (already present).

**Design doc:** `docs/plans/2026-06-04-universal-regression-test-design.md` (commit `3634aa8`). Companion to the existing `docs/design/01_�떆�뒪�뀥�꽕怨�.md` describing the Scenario domain.

